        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 10 at 5:03PM CDT until July 10 at 5:45PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Loves Park,
moving northeast at 20 mph. Spotters have reported quarter sized
hail with this storm.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Poplar Grove, Loves Park, Candlewick Lake, Rockford, Machesney Park,
Timberlane, Roscoe, Caledonia, and Cherry Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
